title: For Sale/Trade:  Complete AR15 Lower - Upgraded and negotiable
postcontent:
You can mount this to your PSA complete upper or Red X Arms and go shooting today. This is a GPI "Dragon" Lower (like Centerfire has for $80) with a number of nicer options. As usual, I won't tell you what these parts cost because: you have Google too - and you will see different prices at different times of the year/season/Obama/store/eBay/whatever.

Three accent pieces for your FDE rifle: A LaRue APEG Rough Grip, a CeraKoted FDE Selector, and the MagPul FDE Trigger Guard.

The Lower Parts Kit is from Palmetto and includes their standard Mil-Spec fire control group/trigger. I think their trigger is pretty good for the $30 or so. I have polished this one at contact points with a 6000 grit diamond belt for a smoother release. 

 "Fancier" parts are:

LMT SOPMOD stock and LMT buffer tube.

PSA Laser Etched Black buffer and buffer spring.

Troy Ambidexrious QD castle nut mount for your single point or rear two point sling connections.

A Seekins Precision Bolt release - looks good and very functional on my other rifles.

KNS Precision Enhanced Takedown pin. This pin can be completely removed with a "QD style" push button. Can also be secured with a split ring so no one tampers with your setup. Front pivot is PSA.

I'm willing to negotiate if you want a lesser configuration (I've got standard stocks, grips, bolt releases, pins, etc), or if you want me to keep the buffer tube altogether because you are building a pistol. Maybe you want it without the grip and the stock because you have your own preference. I'm game for that. I've got a parts graveyard like everyone else.

I believe the price is pretty close to right as the configuration sits. The lower has not been mounted to a particular lower and was transferred as other (as opposed to rifle).

title: For Sale/Trade:  Ruger P97 DC Stainless .45 ACP UPGRADED w spare mags and parts
postcontent:
This is the classic Ruger P97 DC ( Decocker ) .45 ACP.  It has Williams Gun Sight adjustable fiber optic sights. Even though the pistol has had only light range use I had everthing refit to max out the pistols performance. All springs have been replaced in pistol and magazines. Reduced hammer spring to lighten the DA trigger pull, increased recoil spring to tame the felt recoil and limit wear and tear on the frame. and a 5% increase for all the new magazine springs to insure proper feeding. Friction points and feed ramp have been lightly polished. It also has a Houge/Ruger wrap around grip. Only very light scuffing can be found on the fiberglass filled urethane frame, everything else is 100%.

This pistol is very accurate and reliable... While it's a bit bulky it beats out most 1911s that I own. Feeds anything very well, from 180 to 230 FMJ and HP, it seems to have no issues with even the widest mouth hollow points.  It has a very smooth DA trigger pull with no creep that runs about 8lbs, the SA trigger breaks at roughly 3.5lbs with very little pre travel. The adjustable Williams Gunsight Fire Sights (of Davidson Mi) fiber optic sights catch just the right amount of light indoors or outdoor. 

Package also includes rare and sometimes difficult to find spare parts. 

Package includes
*Sturm, Ruger P97 DC Stainless .45 ACP with 4.2" barrel
*Six 8 round magazines with new +5% springs and new S&R floor plates
